  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Band-pass filter centered at 3000 Hz — the aurora frequency. FilterType=1 (BP) cuts both lows and highs, leaving only the shimmering band where borealis lives. Combined with shimmerFeedback=0.65 (cathedral zone), the result is an alien sky: colored, vertical, impossible. The oscillator almost disappears behind the filter character. LFO2 at 0.03 Hz modulates filter cutoff across 25-second cycles — the auroral curtains shift.",
  "tags": [
    "opensky",
    "aurora",
    "band-pass",
    "alien",
    "shimmer",
    "aether",
    "guru-bin",
    "borealis",
